meanings.definition: To restore compressed data to its original size or format.
meanings.sent1: I need to uncompress this file to see its contents.
meanings.sent2: The software can uncompress the zipped folder for you.
meanings.sent3: Trying to uncompress a file without the right tool is like opening a jar without a lid.
meanings.sent4: Her laughter seemed to uncompress the tension in the room.
meanings.sent5: The magician's trick was to uncompress a large object from a tiny box.

meanings.definition: Not compressed; in an uncompressed state.
meanings.sent1: The image file is in an uncompressed format for better quality.
meanings.sent2: Make sure the video is saved in an uncompressed format for editing.
meanings.sent3: The balloon looked uncompress as it slowly deflated.
meanings.sent4: The room felt uncompress after all the clutter was removed.
meanings.sent5: The fresh air outside felt uncompress compared to the stuffy room.
